English:
@q0Aww I feel so needed!
The best I can make of this is the Progenitor Gate can store specific types of items in a matter buffer that is then transferred to the other gate in the periodic energy pulses being sent back and forth.
You will first need to set a stack size for the matter buffer to look for, then you will need to make sure you have that many items in your personal inventory.
@p9Strangely, it appears the matter buffer is already configured to accept standard <color=#00ff00>Oxygen Bottles</color>, <color=#00ff00>Promethium Hydrocells</color>, and <color=#00ff00>Refined Pentaxid</color>.
I can only assume it scanned you as you approached and reconfigured the buffer for those items.
Once you have filled up the buffer, you can teleport yourself through the gate and retrieve the items from the other gate. Seems like it will save you time from having to teleport back and forth so often.
@p9A few tips for you. It seems the matter buffer will not allow you to do anything if the number of items in your personal inventory are less than the number of items it is looking for, so make sure to change the stack size to match how many items you can carry on you at one time.
It will also not allow you to put more items into it than it can hold, and it's only configured for those specific items so other items you will need to figure out how to transfer on your own.

